table.body:
If you have an assistant dog, you must follow the same rules as for non-assistant dogs.

The Guide Dogs for the Blind Association has written guidelines about [taking registered assistance dogs abroad.](http://www.guidedogs.org.uk/adviceandservices/travel/travel-abroad/ "taking registered assistance dogs abroad"){:rel="external"}

Pets entering the UK on airlines under the PETS scheme must normally be carried in the hold. However, assistance dogs are normally allowed to travel in the cabin with their owner on [approved PETS routes and carriers for assistance dogs.](http://www.defra.gov.uk/wildlife-pets/pets/travel/pets/assistance-dogs/ "approved PETS routes and carriers for assistance dogs"){:rel="external"}

*[PETS]: Pet Travel Scheme
